Delta Central School was the original school located on the current site of Delta Secondary. It started accepting secondary students in . By  the site had expanded to include two separate schools, Delta Junior Secondary and Delta Senior Secondary. These two schools operated side by side until  when they became one school. In  the oldest structure remaining on the site, known as the ''B-Block'' was demolished and the  was built. Delta Secondary as of 2003 has adopted schoolnotes [http://www.schoolnotes.com] as its official homework compendeum. In late summer 2003, DSS finished construction of its newest building; a brand new, seismically upgraded gymnasium. 